verbose_text: In calvarial defect models, they proposed that nondiabetic animals presented with the highest levels of osteopontin and Runx2 mRNA compared with all other groups at dosage of 10 mg/kg XREF_BIBR, and resveratrol significantly affected the levels of expression of bone morphogenetic protein 2, bone morphogenetic protein 7, and osteopontin XREF_BIBR.
